&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIVERPOOL UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THERAPY SERVICES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and skilled occupational therapist to join the Musculoskeletal Occupational Therapy Out-patient Team, at Liverpool University Hospitals- Aintree Site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is a small, specialist, out-patient service that accepts internal tertiary referrals from the Orthopaedic and Rheumatology directorates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service focuses on the restoration of function post orthopaedic trauma and post elective hand surgery, and the maintenance of function and facilitation of successful adaptation to lifestyle disruption as a consequence of long term rheumatic conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic occupational therapist with experience in orthopaedics and rheumatology, and with a willingness to work flexibly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah CollinsEmail addresssarah.collins@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
